'''Derek Torent'''<ref name="DSOTM">''[[Death Star Owner's Technical Manual]]''</ref> was a fair-skinned [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]]<ref name="Blog" /> with [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] and brown [[Eye/Legends|eyes]].<ref name="PotF" /> He<ref name="Blog" /> served as an [[Imperial Navy Trooper/Legends|Imperial Navy trooper]] [[Sergeant/Legends|sergeant]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] fought between the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]]. Prior to the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], Torent was among the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] [[Trooper/Legends|troopers]] assigned to the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]]. [[Death Star Trooper/Legends|Death Star troopers]] such as himself served as [[Security guard/Legends|security guards]], monitoring [[Sensor array/Legends|sensor arrays]], and handling [[Hangar/Legends|hangar]] traffic control.<ref name="Complete Dictionary" />

Torent was a senior watch [[Troop/Legends|trooper]] who served at the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star's]] command center. Vigilant in his duties, he monitored external [[Sensor/Legends|sensor]] data, scanning for Alliance activity. Torent wore the standard [[Imperial military uniforms/Legends|uniform]] for Death Star troopers, along with a [[headset comlink]].<ref name="CCG">{{CCG|set=Special Edition Limited|cardname=Sergeant Torent}}</ref> He wielded an [[E-11 blaster rifle/Legends|E-11 blaster rifle]], and on at least one occasion wore his [[Helmet/Legends|helmet]] over the standard-issue [[Imperial officer's uniform/Legends|Imperial officer's uniform]].<ref name="Kenner">{{KennerCite|set=Star Wars (Kenner toy line)|pack=Death Squad Commander|link=Kenner-F-DeathSquad.asp}}</ref> He also wielded another type of [[Blaster rifle/Legends|blaster rifle]],<ref name="PotF" /> and his eyebrows were gray prior to the Battle of Yavin.<ref name="Complete Dictionary" />

==Behind the scenes==
===Origins and name===
Derek Torent was on the set for [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], the first film of the [[original trilogy]],<ref name="Topps">{{Topps|set=1978 Topps Star Wars Series 4|cardname=Member of the evil Empire|link=https://www.tcdb.com/ViewCard.cfm/sid/72964/cid/5255542/1977-Topps-Star-Wars-245-Member-of-the-evil-Empire}}</ref> although it is difficult to tell if the character appears in the film itself.<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref> Following the film's [[May 25]], [[1977]] release,<ref name="Year by Year">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref> the [[June]] 1977<ref name="Cargo Bay">{{CargoBay|url=browse/245/50-10|text=Coloring/Activity Books}}</ref> ''[[Star Wars Coloring Book]]'' included a picture of Torent.<ref name="Coloring">''[[Star Wars Coloring Book]]''</ref> This article treats the latter book as the first [[in-universe]] ''[[Star Wars]]'' product to include Torent, based on it being difficult to tell if he appears in the ''A New Hope'' film.

The [[November]] [[1998]] ''[[Special Edition Limited]]'' expansion set of [[Decipher]]'s [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]] first coined the "Torent" name for the character.<ref name="CCG" /> He would be later given the first name "Derek" by the ''[[Death Star Owner's Technical Manual]]'', released in [[2013]].<ref name="DSOTM" />

===Inconsistencies and other representations/media===
In [[1978]], [[Kenner Products|Kenner]] made a Torent action figure for the [[Star Wars (Kenner toy line)|''Star Wars'' toy line]]. Originally named "Death Squad Commander,"<ref name="Kenner" /> the figure name was changed to "Star Destroyer Commander" when it was re-released in [[1980]] for the [[Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back (toy line)|''Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back'' toy line]].<ref name="Kenner2">{{KennerCite|set=Star Wars (Kenner toy line)|pack=Death Squad Commander|link=Kenner-F-DeathSquad.asp}}</ref> Because no ''Star Wars'' media has established Torent as being part of a [[Death/Legends|death]] squad or serving on a [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]], this article makes no assumptions of Torent performing either responsibility.

While the original "Death Squad/Star Destroyer Commander" figure showed Torent with black eyebrows,<ref name="Kenner" /><ref name="Kenner2" /> both the [[1998]] Kenner [[Star Wars: The Power of the Force (1995 toy line)|''Star Wars: The Power of the Force'']]<ref name="PotF" /> and the [[2007]] [[Hasbro]] ''[[Star Wars: 30th Anniversary Collection]]'' toy lines depict Torent with brown eyebrows, differing from the gray eyebrows visible in his in-universe production photo.<ref name="Hasbro">{{HasbroCite|set=Star Wars: 30th Anniversary Collection|pack=#13: Death Star Trooper (Imperial Soldier)|altlink=https://www.rebelscum.com/tac13dst.asp}}</ref> In [[2012]], Hasbro also used an edited version of Torent's production photo for the "Imperial Navy Commander" figure in their ''[[Star Wars: The Vintage Collection]]'' toy line.<ref name="Hasbro2">{{HasbroCite|set=Star Wars: The Vintage Collection|pack=#094: Imperial Navy Commander|altlink=https://www.rebelscum.com/TVC-Imperial_Navy_Commander.asp}}</ref>

